00:20:05,390 --> 00:20:10,110
Life in this part of the world...

270
00:20:10,110 --> 00:20:11,879
Is difficult...

271
00:20:11,879 --> 00:20:16,441
Without a lion around...

272
00:20:22,870 --> 00:20:28,030
The last few months...

273
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:33,879
'Av killed any love Oi 'ad for dis nashun...

274
00:20:35,570 --> 00:20:37,917
First time...

275
00:20:41,620 --> 00:20:45,763
First time Ah've felt...

276
00:20:45,763 --> 00:20:50,520
A love for their nashun...

277
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:54,680
Isn't de only tin' dat makes soldiers...

278
00:20:54,680 --> 00:20:58,750
Ah've been blind...

279
00:20:58,750 --> 00:21:03,811
Ter everythin' else dat pushes tren...

280
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:10,070
But...

281
00:21:10,070 --> 00:21:12,332
No longer...

282
00:21:14,850 --> 00:21:18,039
After your father died...

283
00:21:18,212 --> 00:21:19,932
Vishal...

284
00:21:21,340 --> 00:21:25,377
At my age...

285
00:21:25,377 --> 00:21:29,406
I'm not sure how much life there is left in me...

286
00:21:30,580 --> 00:21:33,397
But you...

287
00:21:33,397 --> 00:21:38,864
You've got responsibility... Pari, Laxmi... And Sunanda... They need you...

288
00:21:38,864 --> 00:21:44,726
They need you to forget everything else...

289
00:21:45,180 --> 00:21:46,007
I --

290
00:21:46,007 --> 00:21:48,483
What if --

291
00:21:48,483 --> 00:21:51,861
I'll tell Sunanda.

292
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:55,789
Apply to the Army.

293
00:21:56,060 --> 00:21:58,452
We'll tell Sunanda...

294
00:21:58,452 --> 00:22:01,285
Once you're selected...

295
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:58,881
You're late...

296
00:23:02,030 --> 00:23:03,899
I went --

297
00:23:03,899 --> 00:23:07,050
For lunch -- With this friend...

298
00:23:07,050 --> 00:23:08,938
Sunanda...

299
00:23:11,990 --> 00:23:14,608
Thank you.

300
00:23:17,140 --> 00:23:20,818
You've done me a 'uge favour.

301
00:23:22,568 --> 00:23:25,488
It wasn't a favour...

302
00:23:25,488 --> 00:23:28,198
It was my duty.

303
00:23:42,090 --> 00:23:44,138
That's weird...

304
00:23:44,138 --> 00:23:48,898
Telling me never to do it, but giving your SIL the money right away?

305
00:23:48,898 --> 00:23:52,178
The situation was completely different, Amna...

306
00:23:52,178 --> 00:23:56,958
She was asking for a loan... And <i>she</i> just wanted her share.

307
00:23:56,958 --> 00:23:58,919
Hardly different...

308
00:23:59,150 --> 00:24:02,890
You gave her the compensation you got.

309
00:24:02,890 --> 00:24:05,382
Every penny of it.

310
00:24:05,938 --> 00:24:08,748
Vijay...

311
00:24:08,748 --> 00:24:11,359
Was very attached to the estate...

312
00:24:11,359 --> 00:24:15,159
Every brick is a walk down the memory lane.

313
00:24:15,661 --> 00:24:19,781
Vijay's gone... I couldn't do anything about it...

314
00:24:19,781 --> 00:24:24,922
What'd be left of him for Vishal if we lost the estate?

315
00:24:25,062 --> 00:24:28,580
I just saved his memory... For Vishal...

316
00:24:28,580 --> 00:24:32,870
Vishal and his Granny must've been thankful...

317
00:24:32,870 --> 00:24:40,109
Aye... First time she seemed worried that I was late...

318
00:24:40,630 --> 00:24:45,858
But, to be honest... These things hardly matter now...

319
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:48,288
I understand...

320
00:24:48,428 --> 00:24:52,278
But who cares if it 'matters'?

321
00:24:57,020 --> 00:24:59,568
Someone's...

322
00:24:59,568 --> 00:25:02,338
Proposed to me...

323
00:25:03,414 --> 00:25:05,595
You?

324
00:25:06,450 --> 00:25:11,134
Yeah. I don't know why I'm telling you, but...

325
00:25:11,134 --> 00:25:12,864
Who?

326
00:25:13,054 --> 00:25:14,594
An old friend...

327
00:25:14,594 --> 00:25:17,175
From college...

328
00:25:17,175 --> 00:25:18,396
But...

329
00:25:18,396 --> 00:25:21,487
I was only ever interested in Vijay.

330
00:25:21,487 --> 00:25:24,848
He left for America. Got married.

331
00:25:24,848 --> 00:25:28,890
He's back now that he's divorced... Saw me a few days back...

332
00:25:28,890 --> 00:25:31,458
That's when he proposed...

333
00:25:31,560 --> 00:25:34,270
What are you thinking?
-What d'you think?

334
00:25:34,270 --> 00:25:38,100
I've got three kids! Including a young lad!

335
00:25:39,001 --> 00:25:42,581
How long's it been since Vijay left us?

336
00:25:42,581 --> 00:25:46,552
How can I even think of it?

337
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:49,980
You refused?

338
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:52,005
Again and again...

339
00:25:52,005 --> 00:25:57,677
But he's been calling again and again... And saying the same thing...

340
00:25:57,731 --> 00:26:02,511
I guess there's nothing wrong in thinking about it.

341
00:26:02,672 --> 00:26:05,882
What'd you do in my place?

342
00:26:06,290 --> 00:26:08,200
It's no use.

343
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:13,748
We're all in our own set of circumstances... We face different choices...

344
00:26:13,838 --> 00:26:19,778
If you think it can work out well, you should give it a thought.

345
00:26:21,410 --> 00:26:25,061
It ain't as easy as you think...

346
00:26:25,130 --> 00:26:27,110
I know...

347
00:26:27,110 --> 00:26:29,740
But...

348
00:26:29,740 --> 00:26:33,100
We're different, you and I...

349
00:26:33,330 --> 00:26:38,026
You're an independent working woman... Unlike me...

350
00:26:38,060 --> 00:26:40,591
What about my son? He's a young man now!

351
00:26:40,591 --> 00:26:43,435
And he'll be lost in his own world very soon...

352
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:47,280
You'll be all alone once he starts college...

353
00:26:47,280 --> 00:26:50,868
I'll still have Pari and Laxmi.

354
00:26:53,700 --> 00:26:57,988
In your place... I'd still give it a thought...

355
00:26:58,090 --> 00:26:59,820
Especially...

356
00:26:59,820 --> 00:27:03,630
After everything I've gone through in the last few months...

357
00:27:03,630 --> 00:27:05,958
Everything's changed...

358
00:27:06,518 --> 00:27:07,960
Feels like...

359
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,922
I'm...

360
00:27:09,922 --> 00:27:12,493
All alone...

361
00:27:12,650 --> 00:27:17,561
You don't always need a companion who can take someone's place...

362
00:27:19,122 --> 00:27:20,750
Just one...

363
00:27:20,750 --> 00:27:24,455
Who can fill the void...

364
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:30,841
Who you're not alone with...

365
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,979
Did Aunt call?

366
00:28:08,979 --> 00:28:11,359
After she left for Canada?

367
00:28:11,470 --> 00:28:14,088
Why'd she call us nigh?

368
00:28:14,550 --> 00:28:16,889
She wanted 'er share...

369
00:28:16,889 --> 00:28:19,820
She got it.

370
00:28:19,820 --> 00:28:21,981
End av scayle.

371
00:28:22,171 --> 00:28:26,331
I've applied to the Army, by the way.

372
00:28:28,980 --> 00:28:31,138
Aren't you happy?

373
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:57,319
Sarah?

374
00:28:59,980 --> 00:29:02,167
Can I talk to her?

375
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:09,037
Gotta apologise ter someone... Mind?

376
00:29:09,408 --> 00:29:10,880
Aye...

377
00:29:12,550 --> 00:29:16,581
You got back <i>so</i> quickly, Nawab...

378
00:29:16,581 --> 00:29:19,580
Told you about the wedding...

379
00:29:19,580 --> 00:29:25,681
You remember everything after you get there, don't you? Repairs, wedding, and all...

380
00:29:26,140 --> 00:29:28,298
Could you give me the spoon?

381
00:29:42,740 --> 00:29:47,470
Blend these nicely, okay? I'll be back...

382
00:29:50,280 --> 00:29:51,378
Hello?

383
00:29:51,378 --> 00:29:52,350
Hello.

384
00:29:52,350 --> 00:29:55,160
Sorry I didn't call you. Thought you'd be busy.

385
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:57,311
I'm making a cake!

386
00:29:57,311 --> 00:29:58,800
Uh...

387
00:29:58,975 --> 00:30:03,545
Granny wants to talk...

388
00:30:04,310 --> 00:30:06,000
Your Granny?

389
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:07,040
Why?

390
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:10,851
No idea. Find out yourself. Here...

391
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:14,878
Hello?

392
00:30:15,128 --> 00:30:17,142
Hello...
-Sarah...

393
00:30:17,142 --> 00:30:19,323
How are you, love?

394
00:30:19,560 --> 00:30:22,181
Great... And you?

395
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:25,489
I -- I'm fine, dear...

396
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:27,670
I...

397
00:30:27,670 --> 00:30:31,475
I wanted to say sorry...

398
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:36,880
Oi said a lot Oi shouldn't 'av...

399
00:30:37,070 --> 00:30:45,058
It's okay... I get it... My Granny and Grandpa react the same way too, sometimes...

400
00:30:46,340 --> 00:30:48,638
Would you like to talk to Granny?

401
00:30:48,638 --> 00:30:50,309
Why not?

402
00:30:51,040 --> 00:30:53,548
Vishal's Granny... Wants to talk to you...

403
00:30:53,548 --> 00:30:55,158
Why?

404
00:30:55,460 --> 00:30:57,828
What've you done this time?

405
00:30:57,828 --> 00:31:01,540
Why does she want to talk to me? She in the mood to pick another row?

406
00:31:01,540 --> 00:31:03,138
Why does she want to talk to me? She in the mood to pick another row?
-Just -- Talk to her once?

407
00:31:03,138 --> 00:31:04,718
Just -- Talk to her once?

408
00:31:11,340 --> 00:31:14,670
Aye?
-Hello...

409
00:31:15,911 --> 00:31:17,742
Hello...

410
00:31:17,742 --> 00:31:19,260
I...

411
00:31:19,260 --> 00:31:22,611
Wanted to say sorry...

412
00:31:22,611 --> 00:31:24,693
For everything...

413
00:31:24,693 --> 00:31:27,863
I said that day...

414
00:31:31,060 --> 00:31:32,510
Aye...

415
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:35,145
That's what I told Sarah's Grandpa...

416
00:31:35,145 --> 00:31:37,776
We said a lot we shouldn't have...

417
00:31:37,776 --> 00:31:39,387
They're kids...

418
00:31:39,387 --> 00:31:40,727
Big deal...

419
00:31:40,727 --> 00:31:43,730
But we should know better than act like kids!

420
00:31:43,730 --> 00:31:46,680
Absolutely...

421
00:31:47,810 --> 00:31:50,889
Me emoshuns got de better av me...

422
00:31:50,889 --> 00:31:56,568
Oi'm sure yer understan'... Losin' Vijay 'as been most painful...

423
00:31:58,110 --> 00:31:59,747
Aye...

424
00:32:01,440 --> 00:32:03,948
You're telling me...

425
00:32:04,077 --> 00:32:07,300
Sherali left us all grieving...

426
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:09,478
They lef...

427
00:32:09,478 --> 00:32:12,688
Too young...

428
00:32:12,858 --> 00:32:16,260
If anyone should've gone, 'tis us...

429
00:32:16,260 --> 00:32:18,088
Aye...

430
00:32:19,008 --> 00:32:26,347
That's what I think too... May God never make parents live to see the deaths of their children...

431
00:32:26,347 --> 00:32:29,317
Me warrld feels... Empty...

432
00:32:29,317 --> 00:32:31,788
Nothing's ever felt de seem...

433
00:32:31,788 --> 00:32:34,819
Since Vijay's death...

434
00:32:35,340 --> 00:32:40,048
Of course... He was at the border...

435
00:32:40,048 --> 00:32:41,908
But we knew...

436
00:32:41,908 --> 00:32:44,519
He was there... He was alright...

437
00:32:44,519 --> 00:32:47,380
Even as he put his life on the line...

438
00:32:48,789 --> 00:32:53,709
Where in Pakistan are you from, by the way?

439
00:32:53,940 --> 00:32:55,383
Me?

440
00:32:55,383 --> 00:32:57,637
I'm from Lahore.

441
00:32:57,637 --> 00:33:00,767
Sarah's Grandpa's from Amritsar though.

442
00:33:00,767 --> 00:33:02,757
Amritsar?

443
00:33:03,050 --> 00:33:03,921
Bli

444
00:33:03,921 --> 00:33:04,762
Blimey...

445
00:33:04,762 --> 00:33:06,800
That's wha we are!

446
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:10,440
Mum, Da... Everyone lived in Amritsar...

447
00:33:10,440 --> 00:33:15,090
In dat case, Oi gotta ask 'imself! An' Vishal's Grandpa?

448
00:33:15,090 --> 00:33:19,780
Me 'usban' wus from Pakistan... Jhelum, aye...

449
00:33:19,780 --> 00:33:21,740
That's wha 'e wus from...

450
00:33:21,740 --> 00:33:26,660
'E 'ad family dare too... Mamai, Da, Uncles, Aunts...

451
00:33:26,660 --> 00:33:30,980
